WEBVTT

00:08.810 --> 00:10.810
<i> Previously on</i>
So Help Me Todd...

00:10.845 --> 00:12.746
I am a private detective.
You were.

00:12.781 --> 00:13.813
I lost my job.

00:13.848 --> 00:15.518
Two years ago.

00:15.553 --> 00:16.519
TODD:
<i> Mom, are you okay?</i>

00:16.554 --> 00:18.818
I think Harry has left me.

00:18.853 --> 00:20.259
HARRY:
<i> Your mother loves you.</i>

00:20.294 --> 00:21.821
Why do you think
she spent two years

00:21.856 --> 00:23.823
fighting the city, trying
to reinstate your license?

00:23.858 --> 00:25.330
There is one thing
I could do for you

00:25.365 --> 00:26.595
to help you get back
on your feet.

00:26.630 --> 00:29.235
You're a detective again.
An investigator.

00:29.270 --> 00:30.665
And this is your bus pass.

00:30.700 --> 00:32.370
TODD:
<i> I will wear the tie,</i>

00:32.405 --> 00:35.406
but I will not take the bus.

00:36.706 --> 00:39.509
♪ Gotta get up, gotta get out ♪

00:39.544 --> 00:42.446
♪ Gotta get home
before the morning comes ♪

00:42.481 --> 00:44.217
(elevator bell chimes)
♪ What if I'm late? ♪

00:44.252 --> 00:46.549
♪ Got a big date,
gotta get home ♪

00:46.584 --> 00:47.880
♪ Before the sun comes up ♪

00:47.915 --> 00:50.619
♪ Up and away, got a big day ♪

00:50.654 --> 00:53.622
♪ Sorry, can't stay,
I gotta run, run, yeah ♪

00:53.657 --> 00:56.163
♪ Gotta get home,
pick up the phone ♪

00:56.198 --> 00:59.232
♪ Gotta let the people know
I'm gonna be late ♪

01:01.368 --> 01:03.896
(shutter clicking rapidly)

01:03.931 --> 01:05.634
♪ There was a time... ♪

01:05.669 --> 01:08.538
Not today, pal.

01:08.573 --> 01:10.672
Okay, so the DuBois trial
begins today.
Mm-hmm.

01:10.707 --> 01:13.378
You had 9:30, 10:45
and noon meetings,

01:13.413 --> 01:14.775
but I'm guessing...
Yes. Thank you.

01:14.810 --> 01:16.810
Shift everything
to next week, Francey.

01:16.845 --> 01:18.614
The mayor is coming at 11:00,

01:18.649 --> 01:20.880
and I need a little
more time to prepare.

01:20.915 --> 01:23.652
♪ We never thought
it'd grow cold ♪

01:23.687 --> 01:24.917
♪ But now... ♪

01:24.952 --> 01:26.919
Excuse me, sir,
can I help you?

01:26.954 --> 01:28.657
Yeah, I work here.
Excuse me?

01:28.692 --> 01:30.758
I work here. My mother
Margaret Wright works here,

01:30.793 --> 01:32.397
and I work for her.
RECEPTIONIST:
No, you don't.

01:32.432 --> 01:34.795
Yep, it's true.
I work for my mother.

01:34.830 --> 01:35.796
You can't go down there.

01:35.831 --> 01:37.534
I work for my mother.

01:37.569 --> 01:38.766
Security!

01:38.801 --> 01:40.702
Skadden McNeil.
Friday?
Tuesday.

01:40.737 --> 01:42.506
Are you attending
the deposition?
Yes.

01:42.541 --> 01:44.772
Is Hirschland settling?
Never.

01:44.807 --> 01:46.345
Thank you, Francey.

01:46.380 --> 01:48.281
♪ She never even knew
a sailor before ♪

01:48.316 --> 01:49.942
♪ And those were happier days ♪

01:49.977 --> 01:51.878
♪ But now ♪
Yes.

01:51.913 --> 01:54.881
♪ Gotta get up, gotta get out ♪

01:54.916 --> 01:57.356
♪ Gotta get home
before the morning comes ♪
Ow!

01:57.391 --> 02:00.194
Oh, man.
♪ What if I'm late?
Got a big date ♪

02:00.229 --> 02:03.560
♪ Gotta get home
before the sun comes up ♪

02:03.595 --> 02:05.661
♪ Up and away, got a big day ♪

02:05.696 --> 02:07.201
♪ Sorry, can't stay ♪

02:07.236 --> 02:09.269
♪ I gotta run, run, yeah ♪
Yes.

02:09.304 --> 02:10.897
♪ Gotta get home,
pick up the phone ♪

02:10.932 --> 02:13.636
♪ Gotta let the people know
I'm gonna be late ♪

02:13.671 --> 02:15.935
Lyle? Hey.

02:15.970 --> 02:17.475
Top o' the morning, partner.

02:17.510 --> 02:18.608
No food in here.

02:18.643 --> 02:21.215
I don't have any.
I'm just...

02:21.250 --> 02:24.680
Which office was Nadia's,
the investigator I'm replacing?

02:24.715 --> 02:26.253
That office has been repurposed

02:26.288 --> 02:28.222
as a hold site for
closed case files,

02:28.257 --> 02:30.455
broken office equipment
and junk.

02:30.490 --> 02:33.359
Oh, junk. Okay. All right.

02:33.394 --> 02:35.559
So, uh, where's my office?

02:38.861 --> 02:40.861
LYLE:
And so, first things first.

02:40.896 --> 02:42.731
This cabinet in particular is
off-limits to you.

02:42.766 --> 02:43.897
Do not open it.

02:43.932 --> 02:44.931
The lights are
motion-activated,

02:44.966 --> 02:46.702
so this switch does nothing.

02:46.737 --> 02:49.936
And until a cubicle opens up,
this will have to do.

02:49.971 --> 02:51.938
Well, do I get a chair?

02:56.549 --> 02:58.945
Top o' the morning, partner.

03:01.587 --> 03:03.455
What am I, a tailor?

03:04.557 --> 03:06.854
Ridiculous.

03:08.429 --> 03:09.428
(scoffs)

03:09.463 --> 03:11.265
(footfalls approaching)

03:18.571 --> 03:19.933
Oh.

03:26.381 --> 03:29.316
And I guess I'll see you in
an hour for the deposition.

03:29.351 --> 03:30.911
Thanks, Susan.

03:30.946 --> 03:32.715
(chuckles)

03:32.750 --> 03:34.981
I mean, hey, he could have
put you in the parking lot.

03:35.016 --> 03:36.917
Or the restroom.
Yeah, or in hell.

03:36.952 --> 03:39.359
(chuckles)

03:39.394 --> 03:42.461
Wow, that ring really is
a supernova.

03:42.496 --> 03:44.760
You were never getting
anything like that from me.

03:45.763 --> 03:47.796
(both chuckle)

03:50.669 --> 03:52.504
So, are you excited
for your mom's big case?

03:52.539 --> 03:53.835
What big case?

03:53.870 --> 03:55.408
The mayor sex scandal thing.

03:55.443 --> 03:58.477
What mayor sex scandal thing?

03:58.512 --> 04:00.413
Todd, the mayor
of Portland

04:00.448 --> 04:02.316
and the woman accusing him
of a lurid affair?

04:02.351 --> 04:04.010
A lurid affair?

04:04.045 --> 04:06.045
He's denying it.

04:06.080 --> 04:07.948
His wife is pulling
an Alicia Florrick

04:07.983 --> 04:09.653
and standing by him.

04:09.688 --> 04:11.358
But Lexy here claims that
things were hot and heavy,

04:11.393 --> 04:13.591
and she has some of the mayor's
personal items as proof.

04:13.626 --> 04:15.593
Now she's suing him
for breach of contract.

04:15.628 --> 04:16.990
$5 million.

04:17.025 --> 04:18.365
Wait, this is my mom's case?

04:19.267 --> 04:21.830
And I'll be working it?
As an investigator.

04:21.865 --> 04:25.097
Me. A big scandal
with the mayor?!

04:25.132 --> 04:26.703
Well, you were hired to work
her cases, and this is...

04:26.738 --> 04:28.738
Yes! I'm back!

04:35.516 --> 04:37.010
Mom, amazing.

04:37.045 --> 04:38.484
Big scandal, so exciting.

04:38.519 --> 04:39.782
Okay, I'm already
diving into it.

04:39.817 --> 04:41.850
And this mayor seems
super sketchy to me.

04:41.885 --> 04:44.358
I mean, look at that.
Can they be real?

04:44.393 --> 04:47.625
(scoffs)
There's got to be some
serious dark secrets in there.

04:47.660 --> 04:49.121
Maybe he's got some people

04:49.156 --> 04:51.464
chained up in a subterranean
basement somewhere.

04:51.499 --> 04:52.729
Todd?
Huh?

04:52.764 --> 04:54.434
The mayor is our client.

04:54.469 --> 04:56.964
We are defending him
at all costs.

04:56.999 --> 04:58.999
Okay.
But is that one of
the ties I bought you?

04:59.034 --> 05:01.067
(laughs)
You look very handsome.

05:01.102 --> 05:02.706
Yeah, without the tie.

05:02.741 --> 05:03.608
Wait, what do you mean
we're defending the mayor

05:03.643 --> 05:04.873
at all costs?

05:04.908 --> 05:06.138
Like, even if he did it?

05:06.173 --> 05:07.843
Even if he's a psychopath

05:07.878 --> 05:09.812
and throwing baby bunnies
into campfires?

05:09.847 --> 05:10.879
Yes.
Okay.

05:10.914 --> 05:12.419
Fine. Then I'll start

05:12.454 --> 05:15.114
with the woman Lexy Fawcett.

05:15.149 --> 05:17.688
I'll watch her, I'll tail her.
I'll quietly surveil her.

05:17.723 --> 05:19.525
Hey, does having this job
allow me to make

05:19.560 --> 05:20.856
law-abiding citizen's arrests?

05:20.891 --> 05:22.154
Todd.
Uh-huh?

05:22.189 --> 05:24.827
This is a very
important day for me.

05:24.862 --> 05:28.501
I have worked here
for over 17 years.

05:28.536 --> 05:31.097
I generate 31%
of this firm's income.

05:31.132 --> 05:34.672
And now it is time
for the senior partners

05:34.707 --> 05:38.643
to recognize my value
and put my name above that door.

05:38.678 --> 05:43.417
Crest, Folding, Song and Wright.

05:43.452 --> 05:46.178
Which is why I need to tap
all my resources

05:46.213 --> 05:47.553
and clear the mayor's name

05:47.588 --> 05:48.587
and win this case.

05:48.622 --> 05:50.490
Great. Where do I start?

05:50.525 --> 05:52.151
There's a woman
in Southeast Portland

05:52.186 --> 05:53.658
named Jacqueline DuBois.

05:53.693 --> 05:55.088
Her basement flooded
because of

05:55.123 --> 05:56.628
the city water main break,

05:56.663 --> 05:58.597
and many, many of her
belongings were damaged.

05:58.632 --> 06:00.126
Okay. Okay.

06:00.161 --> 06:02.733
And I need you to go down
and observe that trial.

06:02.768 --> 06:04.438
I want to know everything.

06:04.473 --> 06:06.132
Evidence, witnesses, testimony.

06:06.167 --> 06:07.903
This is your first case,

06:07.938 --> 06:09.971
and I am sure
you're going to ace it.

06:10.006 --> 06:13.106
Wait. Where's the high-profile
sex scandal in this assignment?

06:13.141 --> 06:14.943
That's what I'll be doing.

06:14.978 --> 06:17.044
You are doing the legwork
for my next case

06:17.079 --> 06:18.584
when I represent
Jacqueline's neighbors

06:18.619 --> 06:20.014
in a very similar lawsuit.

06:20.049 --> 06:21.818
What?!
Mm-hmm.

06:21.853 --> 06:24.986
I took this job
to work real cases.

06:25.021 --> 06:27.857
No, I gave you this job
because you are broke.

06:27.892 --> 06:30.728
I want murders, kidnapping,
blackmail, not water damage.

06:30.763 --> 06:33.863
I mean, who-who's investigating
the mayor, the woman, the sex?

06:33.898 --> 06:36.503
Here's the preliminary report
on Alexis "Lexy" Fawcett.

06:36.538 --> 06:38.472
I'll have more
on her financials in a moment.

06:38.507 --> 06:40.606
Excellent. Thank you, Lyle.

06:41.609 --> 06:44.940
Him? Poindexter?

06:44.975 --> 06:46.546
Todd, you're still
learning the ropes here,

06:46.581 --> 06:48.009
and this is the mayor.

06:48.044 --> 06:49.516
We need our top people on this.

06:49.551 --> 06:50.880
I'm not one of your top people?!

06:50.915 --> 06:52.486
My top people don't show up
33 minutes late.

06:52.521 --> 06:54.686
Who told you I was thir...?

06:54.721 --> 06:56.556
Oh, my God.

06:56.591 --> 06:57.887
Mom, this is crazy.

06:57.922 --> 07:00.186
You can't stick me
with this dead-end case!

07:00.221 --> 07:02.694
Todd, Jacqueline's trial
is at 10:00 a.m.
Don't Todd me, Margaret.

07:02.729 --> 07:04.729
You will not be
late to that, too,
if you want a ride home

07:04.764 --> 07:05.862
tonight from your mother.
Your ace detective
went out of his way

07:05.897 --> 07:07.061
to find your missing husband?

07:08.702 --> 07:11.505
Fine. Have fun
with your hall monitor.

07:15.709 --> 07:19.942
Alistair Song wants to see you
in the conference room. Now.

07:21.814 --> 07:23.979
Alistair.

07:24.014 --> 07:26.850
Hello, Margaret. Have a seat.

07:26.885 --> 07:28.720
Thank you.

07:28.755 --> 07:31.756
You know, I was just
mentioning you

07:31.791 --> 07:33.593
and my position here...

07:33.628 --> 07:35.056
What's this about

07:35.091 --> 07:36.695
you hiring your son?

07:36.730 --> 07:38.290
My son?
Wasn't he involved

07:38.325 --> 07:42.261
in some illegal
wiretapping situation

07:42.296 --> 07:45.836
a few years ago?
And now he's working here?

07:45.871 --> 07:48.036
Yes. My son. Todd.

07:48.071 --> 07:50.973
Well, as I'm sure you know,
we had an opening

07:51.008 --> 07:52.271
in the investigations
department,

07:52.306 --> 07:54.009
and he was cleared

07:54.044 --> 07:56.308
of those charges
that you mentioned.

07:56.343 --> 07:59.817
Todd is an excellent detective.

07:59.852 --> 08:02.787
I have seen his work up close.

08:02.822 --> 08:04.657
Very close.

08:04.692 --> 08:08.694
But can we trust him
not to embarrass us?

08:09.697 --> 08:11.994
Yes, we can trust him.

08:12.029 --> 08:15.866
In fact, now that I'll be busy
with the mayor's case, I...

08:15.901 --> 08:17.934
The mayor's case?

08:17.969 --> 08:20.101
Uh, yes.

08:20.136 --> 08:22.268
The mayor, the scandal. I...

08:22.303 --> 08:24.974
Margaret, I'll be taking lead
on the mayor's case.

08:25.009 --> 08:27.614
I've already spoken
to his office, and...
What?

08:27.649 --> 08:29.748
Uh, he's my client.

08:29.783 --> 08:32.245
I-I joined the board
of the art museum a year ago

08:32.280 --> 08:34.280
to befriend his wife
and-and bring their business

08:34.315 --> 08:36.887
to this firm.
He's only...
Margaret.

08:36.922 --> 08:38.889
It's the mayor.

08:38.924 --> 08:41.122
We need our top people on this.

08:43.159 --> 08:46.600
You've come so far
here, Margaret.

08:46.635 --> 08:51.132
It seems like just yesterday
that, uh, you were my secretary.

08:51.167 --> 08:52.936
Executive secretary.

08:52.971 --> 08:56.104
And I look forward
to making space for you

08:56.139 --> 08:58.975
here at the top.

08:59.010 --> 09:01.010
Someday.

09:01.045 --> 09:03.782
Alistair,

09:03.817 --> 09:06.983
with all due respect,

09:07.018 --> 09:09.986
I have the relationships,
I've done the background.

09:10.021 --> 09:13.055
This is my case.

09:13.090 --> 09:16.828
Well, um,
maybe you could be useful then.

09:16.863 --> 09:19.127
Uh, as my second chair.

09:19.162 --> 09:20.931
Oh...

09:20.966 --> 09:23.934
I'm so sorry to interrupt,
but the mayor's team is here.

09:23.969 --> 09:26.101
Hey. Hi. We can't wait.
We got to get going

09:26.136 --> 09:27.773
on this, kids, okay?

09:27.808 --> 09:29.643
Oh, Margaret, isn't this awful?

09:29.678 --> 09:32.173
This hideous woman making
horrible accusations.

09:32.208 --> 09:35.209
Thank God you'll be
helping us through this.

09:35.244 --> 09:36.243
(Alistair clears throat)
Oh.

09:36.278 --> 09:39.653
Um, Elaine and Mr. Mayor,

09:39.688 --> 09:41.347
I will be right
by your side.

09:41.382 --> 09:45.758
But-but we have decided that
one of our founding partners

09:45.793 --> 09:50.191
would be better equipped to
handle a case of this magnitude.

09:50.226 --> 09:53.392
This is... Alistair Song.

09:53.427 --> 09:55.130
It's a pleasure to meet you.
Mr. Mayor.

09:55.165 --> 09:58.166
Under very strange
circumstances.

09:58.201 --> 09:59.805
This is my campaign manager
Moe Simms.

09:59.840 --> 10:01.268
Yeah, okay.

10:01.303 --> 10:03.072
We got an election in four
short weeks, my friends.

10:05.373 --> 10:08.044
I want to assure you all
that we will mount

10:08.079 --> 10:11.311
a strong defense against this
flimsy, opportunistic lawsuit.

10:11.346 --> 10:12.884
MOE:
That's right.

10:12.919 --> 10:15.689
So, how are we
gonna bury her?

10:15.724 --> 10:18.219
Uh, well, we have our tried
and true means and, uh...

10:18.254 --> 10:21.222
Breach of oral contract
is very difficult to establish

10:21.257 --> 10:24.357
unless there's written proof
that the mayor was planning

10:24.392 --> 10:26.997
to financially support her
or leave his wife.

10:27.032 --> 10:29.164
Uh, Margaret, I've never
actually met this woman.

10:29.199 --> 10:30.836
I never promised
to leave my wife.

10:30.871 --> 10:32.739
None of this is true.

10:32.774 --> 10:35.775
We'll overwhelm her with
an expensive countersuit,

10:35.810 --> 10:39.174
and she'll fold,
I guarantee it.

10:40.177 --> 10:41.341
And?

10:42.344 --> 10:43.915
And?

10:43.950 --> 10:46.445
We have already requested
an ex parte hearing

10:46.480 --> 10:48.447
for later this afternoon.
Of course,

10:48.482 --> 10:50.185
you won't have to be there.
ALISTAIR:
That's right.

10:50.220 --> 10:52.055
But she will.

10:52.090 --> 10:53.859
I want this woman
to have to come down

10:53.894 --> 10:56.862
and face the judge.
(crying)

10:58.294 --> 11:02.263
Oh, Elaine. Elaine, shh.
It's okay. It's okay.

11:02.298 --> 11:04.837
It'll be all right.

11:04.872 --> 11:07.301
We will get through this.

11:07.336 --> 11:09.842
Together.

11:09.877 --> 11:15.309
Now, this is Christine "Chrissy"
De Pointe, a Parisian flapper,

11:15.344 --> 11:19.082
and she was made in 1935

11:19.117 --> 11:21.381
from very fine,
delicate porcelain.

11:21.416 --> 11:25.957
Now, can you see this little
brown stain here on her skirt?

11:25.992 --> 11:27.453
Here, right here,

11:27.488 --> 11:29.191
down near the hem?

11:29.226 --> 11:32.095
That was caused
by the water damage.

11:32.130 --> 11:34.328
This doll used to be worth

11:34.363 --> 11:37.034
at least $250,

11:37.069 --> 11:39.432
and now she's garbage.

11:40.234 --> 11:45.141
Your Honor, that was exhibit
number nine of... 117

11:45.176 --> 11:47.044
exhibits.

11:52.018 --> 11:53.985
Don't... die.

11:54.020 --> 11:57.153
No. This-this is your fault.

11:57.188 --> 11:59.287
This is not my fault.

11:59.322 --> 12:00.992
You dragged me into this.

12:01.027 --> 12:02.928
Lexy?

12:02.963 --> 12:05.326
You never said anything about
me getting hauled into court.

12:05.361 --> 12:09.429
You promised me 20,000 bucks.

12:09.464 --> 12:11.497
I only did this
for the money.

12:11.532 --> 12:14.170
Look... I have to go in

12:14.205 --> 12:15.809
and see some
stupid judge now.

12:15.844 --> 12:18.240
I'm done. Bye.

12:20.981 --> 12:23.014
(sighs)

12:29.957 --> 12:32.155
(whispering):
What are you doing here?

12:32.190 --> 12:33.189
(whispering):
I'm just...

12:33.224 --> 12:35.257
(mouthing)

12:36.260 --> 12:37.556
Go.

12:37.591 --> 12:39.129
(whispering):
Okay. I'm going.

12:39.164 --> 12:43.001
Back to the Valley
of the Dolls.

12:43.036 --> 12:45.069
TODD:
<i> Allison, can you believe</i>

12:45.104 --> 12:48.204
Mom stuck me with this junk
case? Me? She doesn't value me.

12:48.239 --> 12:50.239
She doesn't trust me.
After what I did for her?

12:50.274 --> 12:53.011
I have incredible skills
that are just being ignored.

12:53.046 --> 12:55.079
117 dolls. Give me a break.

12:55.114 --> 12:57.081
Yeah, but you're earning money,
you're working.

12:57.116 --> 13:00.150
Maybe you can get out of my
garage in, like, maybe a month,

13:00.185 --> 13:01.613
you think?
Let's not get ahead
of ourselves.

13:01.648 --> 13:05.254
This is about respect,
of which she is giving me none.

13:05.289 --> 13:07.091
Maybe the way to look at this

13:07.126 --> 13:09.126
is, you've reached
a crossroads in life.
Uh-huh.

13:09.161 --> 13:10.930
You hit bottom.
I haven't hit bottom!

13:10.965 --> 13:14.098
You lost your P.I. license
and you almost went to jail.

13:14.133 --> 13:16.298
Oh, my God. I've hit bottom.

13:16.333 --> 13:18.003
But now you're working your way
back up,

13:18.038 --> 13:21.171
and this job is a lifeline,
okay?

13:21.206 --> 13:24.174
So you need to suck it up,
pull yourself together,

13:24.209 --> 13:25.604
and stick it out.

13:25.639 --> 13:27.144
So you're saying I need...

13:27.179 --> 13:29.278
to find myself in this job?

